6. "What Am I Missing?"
Multi-account support. Enterprise Snowflake deployments have 5-50 accounts. This app is single-account. Leadership will ask "what about our other accounts?" on day one.

Data retention and GDPR. The mart stores alert history, query text, user activity. What's the retention policy? Is there PII in query text? Who can see other users' queries?

Disaster recovery. If DBA_MAINT_DB goes down, the monitoring app goes down. There's no failover, no read replica, no degraded mode beyond the offline_capable flag.

Version management. 167 files with no visible versioning strategy beyond CONFIG_VERSION and THEME_VERSION. How do you roll back a bad deploy?

Concurrent users. Streamlit session state is per-user. But the underlying queries hit shared ACCOUNT_USAGE views. At 20 concurrent users, you'll generate significant compute load from the monitoring tool itself.

Compliance frameworks. No SOC2, HIPAA, or insurance-industry regulatory mapping. For ALFA Insurance, auditors will ask "how does this support our compliance posture?" and there's no answer.

Change management audit trail. The Action Queue and alert suppressions appear to modify state. Where's the audit log of who did what and when?

Dependency on Snowflake internals. ACCOUNT_USAGE view schemas change between Snowflake releases. One column rename breaks the app. No defensive schema validation exists.

